ComicInfo.Summary: FeFo#63 All Color!!! It's GTS mania as manipulative Stella Stargaze volunteers her new pal (stooge) Garganta to help out a beleagured movie crew dealing with a tempermental actress. "The Assualt Of The 60 Foot Woman" suddenly has real life giantess Gaganta in the lead and everything goes swimmingly until the jealous former star slips Big G a stimulant mickey, and the giant woman goes on the prerequisite rampage. It takes Synn, Microman, and a high-voltage jolt from new heroine Rayda(she's a stuntwoman in civilian life, you see, and had been working on the set) to slow her down. But , though Garganta may be down, she is definitely not out... Story by Bill Black, drawn by Black and Tom Moser, inks by Nar Castro and Sonny de los Santos. Guest starring Mike Frankovich, Jr., John Carl Buechler, Rory Calhoun, and featuring the first appearance of Marla Allison. Page after page of wild, giant rampaging woman action. Color cover by Brad Gorby and Mark Heike, full color throughout. Standard comic book format.
ComicInfo.Title: Assault of the 60 Foot Woman!
